==Starting off==
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Oh no, why today of all days?
* '''Player:''' What's wrong Mr Rabbit?
* '''Easter Bunny:''' I'm having an eggceptionally bad day. But if you must know my Egg making machine is shell dry and the next shipment of fuel will not be here for a while!
* '''Easter Bunny:''' I would love it if a cracking adventurer, such as yourself would help a Bunny in need.
* {{tselect|Will you help the Easter Bunny?}}
* {{topt|Yes}}
** '''Player:''' I would love to help you mix up some more fuel.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Thanks for eggreeing to help me.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' There are three ingredients that are needed to make the fuel.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' The first ingredient is Dried cocoa. During any other time of year this ingredient would be eggceptionally hard to get.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' But if I'm spot on with my information, there should be a merchant rolling into Al Kharid soon. He should sell you some.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Try not to bring me camel dung, they do look similar.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' The second ingredient is really high quality milk.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' The most eggceptional milk around has got to be milk from Hosidius, I'm sure Duke Horacio's cook can help you out.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' The third ingredient is some cracking spices, very special ones. Can't go into detail, trade secret and all.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' I'm sure if you talk to Martin in Draynor, he'll be a good egg and help you out if you ask for Special spices.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Since you're doing my errands for me. Feel free to use my tunnels to get around.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' But don't make a yolk out of it, you may only use each tunnel once. Can't have you interrupting my workers any more than that.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Also, if you ever forgot what you need, there will be a worker nearby who can remind you.
** '''Player:''' I'll get right on it. Be back soon.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' See you soon!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No}}
** '''Player:''' Get stuffed.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' I'll have you know this is no yolking matter.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Easter Bunny again===
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Where do I get the Dried cocoa?}}
** '''Player:''' Where do I get the Dried cocoa?
** '''Easter Bunny:''' During any other time of year this ingredient would be a nightmare to get.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' But if I'm spot on with my information, there should be a merchant making his way from the Kharidian Desert to Al Kharid.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' I'd suggest checking the Shantay Pass.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Where do I get the bottle of Hosidius milk?}}
** '''Player:''' Where do I get the bottle of Hosidius milk?
** '''Easter Bunny:''' The most eggceptional milk around has got to be milk from Hosidius, I'm sure Duke Horacio's cook in Lumbridge castle can help you out.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Where do I get the Special spices?}}
** '''Player:''' Where do I get the Special spices?
** '''Easter Bunny:''' I'm sure if you talk to Martin in Draynor, he'll be a good egg and help you out if you ask for Special spices.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' He should get the hint.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Goodbye.}}
** {{tmissing}}

==Dried cocoa==
===Talking to Egg===
* '''Egg:''' You need to find the Travelling Merchant to get the Dried cocoa.
* '''Egg:''' Now hop along and go get the cocoa.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Travelling merchant===
* '''Travelling merchant:''' Hello there stranger.
* {{tselect|What would you like to talk about?}}
* {{topt|Ask about the merchant.}}
** '''Player:''' I haven't seen you around here, where are you from?
** '''Travelling merchant:''' I am from a place far in the Kharidian Desert. So far that you would not have heard of it, so there is no point in me telling you the name of this place.
** '''Travelling merchant:''' The reason why you never see me around here often is because I only ever make the trip to Al Kharid around Easter time.
** '''Travelling merchant:''' This is around the time my wares ripen and sell for their highest price.
** {{tact|initial}}
* {{topt|Ask about the dried cocoa.}}
** '''Player:''' Are you the merchant who sells Dried cocoa? I need to get some for the Easter Bunny.
** '''Travelling merchant:''' Well of course, anything for my best customer! But I need to ask a favour of you in return.
** '''Travelling merchant:''' You may know that I only come here around Easter time ever year but I still do not know my way around Al Kharid very well.
** '''Travelling merchant:''' One of the general store workers was supposed to deliver a Crate of baskets to me, but I am yet to receive them.
** '''Travelling merchant:''' Can you please retrieve them for me? I will give you the Dried cocoa in return.
** '''Player:''' I'll get right on it, goodbye.
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Al Kharid shop keeper or shop assistant===
* '''Shop keeper:''' Can I help you at all?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Talk about Easter.}}
** '''Player:''' Do you by chance have the Travelling Merchant's shipment of baskets?
** '''Shop keeper:''' Why yes, I do. But how would you know about the shipment?
** '''Player:''' The Traveling{{sic}} Merchant asked me to pick the shipment up for him. He said something about not knowing Al Kharid very well.
** '''Player:''' Also someone should have delivered the shipment to him earlier today.
** '''Shop keeper:''' Oh yes, I forgot about that. Could you deliver the shipment to him for me?
** '''Player:''' Yes of course, thats{{sic}} why I'm here.
** {{tbox|pic=Crate of baskets detail.png|You receive a Crate of baskets.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Yes please. What are you selling?|event=no}}
* {{topt|No thanks.|event=no}}
* {{topt|What do you think of Ali Morrisane?|event=no}}

===Bringing the merchant the crate===
* '''Travelling merchant:''' Hello there stranger.
* '''Travelling merchant:''' Did you get my shipment of baskets?
* '''Player:''' Yes I did, here you go.
* '''Travelling merchant:''' Thank you very much my new friend, here take this Dried cocoa and give the Easter Bunny my thanks.
* {{tbox|pic=Crate of baskets detail.png|pic2=Dried cocoa detail.png|You hand over the shipment in exchange for some Dried cocoa.}}
* {{tact|end}}

==Hosidius milk==
===Talking to Eg===
* '''Eg:''' You need to get the milk from the cook. He's the one with the white chef's hat, hop to it now!
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Cook===
* {{tselect|What would you like to talk about?}}
* {{topt|Talk about Easter.}}
** '''Player:''' Hello Cook. The Easter Bunny has run out of fuel for his egg making machine and has sent me to ask you for a favour.
** '''Cook:''' I am listening.
** '''Player:''' Do you by chance have any Hosidius milk? The Easter Bunny needs some to make the fuel.
** '''Cook:''' I may have some lying around the kitchen, I would gladly give you some milk for the Easter Bunny.
** '''Cook:''' But first you must answer a riddle. If you get it right, I will give you some Hosidius milk.
** '''Player:''' I would be glad to answer a riddle for you.
** '''Cook:''' Are you ready to answer my riddle?
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Yes.}}
*** '''Player:''' Yes I am ready, crack out your riddle.
*** ''The riddle varies for each player:''
*** {{topt|Riddle 1:}}
**** '''Cook:''' When dark and bitter, drink me warm in the winter.
**** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
**** {{topt|Lemon juice.}}
**** {{topt|Beer.}}
**** {{topt|Sewer water.}}
**** {{topt|Butter.}}
**** {{topt|Chocolate.}}
***** '''Cook:''' Congratulations, that's the right answer.
***** '''Cook:''' Here is the Hosidius milk I promised.
***** {{tbox|pic=Hosidius milk detail.png|You receive a bottle of Hosidius milk.}}
***** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|Riddle 2:}}
**** '''Cook:''' I am round, yet not a perfect sphere. I can be cracked and not have anything inside. What am I?
**** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
**** {{topt|Easter Egg.}}
***** '''Cook:''' Congratulations, that's the right answer.
***** '''Cook:''' Here is the Hosidius milk I promised.
***** {{tbox|pic=Hosidius milk detail.png|You receive a bottle of Hosidius milk.}}
***** {{tact|end}}
**** {{topt|The Grand Exchange.}}
**** {{topt|Cake.}}
**** {{topt|Potato.}}
**** {{topt|Choc-ice.}}
*** {{topt|Riddle 3:}}
